{"ts": "2026-04-21T22:02:00Z", "event": "clarify_critic", "feature": "gate-overnight-pr-creation-on-merged-over-zero", "findings": ["'ZERO PROGRESS' is smuggled in as a literal title; the acceptance criterion says only 'zero-progress title/body' without defining the string.", "Verification path is a disjunction ('integration test (or manual dry-run)') with no commitment to which is required.", "A parallel gh pr create call at runner.sh:1083 for cross-repo PRs uses its own MERGED_COUNT variable; the ticket silently excludes it from scope.", "Scope-by-citation: the ticket asserts scope-boundedness by citing DR-1 in the linked research without the assessment verifying the research.", "Requirements alignment invokes a 'bias toward surfacing failures' design principle that is not quoted from any requirements file.", "Rating alignment High on 'no direct conflict' stretches High to mean 'not disqualified'; no requirement speaks to PR draft state, title content, auto-merge gating, or zero-progress surfacing.", "Value case rests on n=1 (one observed zombie PR); the fix may be aimed at the downstream artifact rather than the upstream failure mode.", "Morning-review workflow already surfaces zero-merge sessions through other channels (morning report, session log); draft PR may be redundant rather than necessary."], "dispositions": {"apply": 2, "dismiss": 6, "ask": 0}, "applied_fixes": ["Added open research question: examine the parallel cross-repo gh pr create at runner.sh:1043-1115 and evaluate whether its existing skip-on-zero pattern should be aligned with the home-repo draft-on-zero design, or whether the asymmetry is deliberate.", "Softened Requirements alignment note from 'positively grounded in requirements/pipeline.md' to 'no-conflict; weak-by-silence — no requirement speaks to PR draft state, so alignment is by absence-of-conflict rather than positive grounding'."], "dismissals": [{"finding_index": 0, "rationale": "The exact title/body string is a spec-phase design detail. Clarify-level intent is clear: create a draft PR signaling zero progress. Downstream spec interview will select the wording."}, {"finding_index": 1, "rationale": "Verification-path choice (test vs manual) is standard spec/plan interview territory; it does not create intent ambiguity at the Clarify stage."}, {"finding_index": 3, "rationale": "Self-resolved against new evidence: read research/orchestrator-worktree-escape/research.md. DR-1 explicitly recommends beta (two-epic split) with reasoning; DR-2 sizes this as a 30-min ticket explicitly outside epic 126. The citation is grounded, not circular."}, {"finding_index": 5, "rationale": "Duplicate of finding_index 4 — same objection about requirements-alignment grounding. Addressed by the Apply revision on finding 4 that softens the alignment wording."}, {"finding_index": 6, "rationale": "Self-resolved against research DR-2: the design choice was explicitly weighed. The ticket is scoped to the downstream PR artifact by design — upstream failures belong to the parent epic 126. n=1 is acceptable framing for a ~30-min fix whose cost profile makes frequency analysis disproportionate."}, {"finding_index": 7, "rationale": "Self-resolved against research DR-2: 'Skipping hides the failure from the morning-review workflow. --draft blocks auto-merge, appears in review queue, and title signals zero progress.' The OPEN-MERGEABLE-CLEAN zombie PR is itself the ongoing operator-attention tax the ticket targets; other channels surface information but do not prevent the wrong-merge risk."}], "status": "ok"}
